The function creates a dictionary to count the occurrences of each character in the first string. It then goes through the second string, decreasing the count of each character. If at any point a character is not found in the dictionary or its count is already 0, the strings are not anagrams.

Finally, the function checks if all counts are 0. If they are, the strings are anagrams.

