Here's a Java program to check if a binary tree is balanced. This program uses the concept of calculating the height of the left and right subtrees and checks whether the difference in their heights is less than or equal to 1.

```java
class Node {
    int key;
    Node left, right;

    public Node(int item) {
        key = item;
        left = right = null;
    }
}

class BinaryTree {

    Node root;

    // Function to find the height of a binary tree
    int height(Node node) {
        if (node == null)
            return 0;
        else
            return (1 + Math.max(height(node.left), height(node.right)));
    }

    // Function to check whether a binary tree is balanced
    boolean isBalanced(Node node) {
        if (node == null)
            return true;

        int lh = height(node.left);
        int rh = height(node.right);

        if (Math.abs(lh - rh) <= 1 && isBalanced(node.left) && isBalanced(node.right))
            return true;

        return false;
    }

