The `find` function is used to find the set of an element i. The `unionSet` function is used to do union of two sets of x and y with the use of union by rank. The `compare` function is a comparator function which is used to sort the edges in non-decreasing order of their weight.

In the `kruskal` function, after creating the disjoint sets, it sorts all the edges. Then it iterates through all the edges, if the source and destination of the current edge are in different sets, it adds the edge to the MST and merges the two sets. This process continues until the MST has (n-1) edges where n is the number of vertices.

