This implementation provides two main functions: `insert` and `extractMin`. The `insert` function adds a new element to the heap by placing it at the end of the array and then "bubbling" it up to maintain the heap property. The `extractMin` function removes and returns the smallest element from the heap by replacing the root with the last element, then "bubbling" it down to maintain the heap property.

The helper functions `siftUp`, `siftDown`, `parent`, `leftChild`, and `rightChild` are used to perform the necessary swapping and index calculations.

