Here's a Java program to check if a binary tree is balanced. This program uses the concept of height difference between left and right subtrees.

```java
class Node {
    int key;
    Node left, right;

    public Node(int item) {
        key = item;
        left = right = null;
    }
}

class BinaryTree {

    Node root;

    boolean isBalanced(Node node) {
        if (node == null)
            return true;

        int lh = height(node.left);
        int rh = height(node.right);

        if (Math.abs(lh - rh) <= 1 && isBalanced(node.left) && isBalanced(node.right))
            return true;

        return false;
    }

