    }
}
```

In this code, we first calculate the height of the left and right subtrees. If the difference between their heights is more than 1, then the tree is not balanced. Otherwise, we recursively check if the left and right subtrees are balanced.

The time complexity of this solution is O(n^2) in the worst case where the tree is completely skewed. This can be improved to O(n) by doing level order traversal and keeping track of the size of subtrees at each level.
